The paper discusses a machine learning algorithm for principal component analysis and singular value decomposition, which are commonly used in the fields of machine learning, computer vision, and data science. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The algorithm also involves stochastic iterations and optimization, which suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper applies the algorithm to an inherently non-convex problem, which may relate to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well.
